  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: dd64eb842f3dd694bae8487ce6510215, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Judgment on Israel\u2019s Neighbors"
      title: "Judgment on Israel\u2019s Neighbors"
      number: 1
      content: '  The words of Amos, who was among the shepherds[[COMMENT(0)]] of
        Tekoa, which he saw concerning Israel in the days of Uzziah king of Judah
        and in the days of Jeroboam the son of Joash, king of Israel, two years before
        the earthquake.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:1 '
        content: 'Or Or '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And he said:  \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> roars from Zionand
        utters his voice from Jerusalem;  the pastures of the shepherds mourn,and
        the top of Carmel withers.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:  \u201CFor three transgressions
        of Damascus,and for four, I will not revoke the punishment,[[COMMENT(0)]]because
        they have threshed Gileadwith threshing sledges of iron.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:3 '
        content: Hebrew ; also verses 6, 9, 11, 13
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  So I will send a fire upon the house of Hazael,and it shall devour
        the strongholds of Ben-hadad.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "I will break the gate-bar of Damascus,and cut off the inhabitants
        from the Valley of Aven,[[COMMENT(0)]]and him who holds the scepter from
        Beth-eden;and the people of Syria shall go into exile to Kir,\u201Dsays the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:5 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:  \u201CFor three transgressions
        of Gaza,and for four, I will not revoke the punishment,because they carried
        into exile a whole peopleto deliver them up to Edom.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So I will send a fire upon the wall of Gaza,and it shall devour her
        strongholds.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "I will cut off the inhabitants from Ashdod,and him who holds the
        scepter from Ashkelon;I will turn my hand against Ekron,and the remnant of
        the Philistines shall perish,\u201Dsays the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:  \u201CFor three transgressions
        of Tyre,and for four, I will not revoke the punishment,because they delivered
        up a whole people to Edom,and did not remember the covenant of brotherhood.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So I will send a fire upon the wall of Tyre,and it shall devour her
        strongholds.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:  \u201CFor three transgressions
        of Edom,and for four, I will not revoke the punishment,  because he pursued
        his brother with the sword  and cast off all pity,  and his anger tore perpetually, 
        and he kept his wrath forever.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So I will send a fire upon Teman,and it shall devour the strongholds
        of Bozrah.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:  \u201CFor three transgressions
        of the Ammonites,and for four, I will not revoke the punishment,because they
        have ripped open pregnant women in Gilead,that they might enlarge their border.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So I will kindle a fire in the wall of Rabbah,  and it shall devour
        her strongholds,with shouting on the day of battle,  with a tempest in the
        day of the whirlwind;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "and their king shall go into exile,he and his princes[[COMMENT(0)]]
        together,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>."
      comments:
      - number: '1:15 '
        content: 'Or '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "  Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:  \u201CFor three transgressions
        of Moab,and for four, I will not revoke the punishment,[[COMMENT(0)]]because
        he burned to limethe bones of the king of Edom.  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:1 '
        content: Hebrew ; also verses 4, 6
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So I will send a fire upon Moab,and it shall devour the strongholds
        of Kerioth,and Moab shall die amid uproar,amid shouting and the sound of
        the trumpet;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: Judgment on Judah'
      title: Judgment on Judah
      number: 3
      content: "  I will cut off the ruler from its midst,and will kill all its princes[[COMMENT(0)]]
        with him,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:3 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:  \u201CFor three transgressions
        of Judah,and for four, I will not revoke the punishment,because they have
        rejected the law of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and have not kept his
        statutes,but their lies have led them astray,those after which their fathers
        walked.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Judgment on Israel'
      title: Judgment on Israel
      number: 5
      content: "So I will send a fire upon Judah,and it shall devour the strongholds
        of Jerusalem.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:  \u201CFor three transgressions
        of Israel,and for four, I will not revoke the punishment,because they sell
        the righteous for silver,and the needy for a pair of sandals\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'those who trample the head of the poor into the dust of the earthand
        turn aside the way of the afflicted;  a man and his father go in to the same
        girl,so that my holy name is profaned;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'they lay themselves down beside every altaron garments taken in pledge,and
        in the house of their God they drinkthe wine of those who have been fined.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CYet it was I who destroyed the Amorite before them,  whose
        height was like the height of the cedarsand who was as strong as the oaks; 
        I destroyed his fruit aboveand his roots beneath.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  Also it was I who brought you up out of the land of Egypt  and
        led you forty years in the wilderness,  to possess the land of the Amorite.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And I raised up some of your sons for prophets,and some of your young
        men for Nazirites.Is it not indeed so, O people of Israel?\u201Ddeclares
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CBut you made the Nazirites drink wine,and commanded the prophets,saying,
        \u2018You shall not prophesy.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CBehold, I will press you down in your place,as a cart full
        of sheaves presses down.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  Flight shall perish from the swift,  and the strong shall not retain
        his strength,  nor shall the mighty save his life;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'he who handles the bow shall not stand,and he who is swift of foot
        shall not save himself,  nor shall he who rides the horse save his life;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "and he who is stout of heart among the mightyshall flee away naked
        in that day,\u201Ddeclares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Israel\u2019s Guilt and Punishment"
      title: "Israel\u2019s Guilt and Punishment"
      number: 1
      content: '    Hear this word that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has spoken
        against you, O people of Israel, against the whole family that I brought
        up out of the land of Egypt:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "  \u201CYou only have I knownof all the families of the earth;  therefore
        I will punish youfor all your iniquities.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CDo two walk together,unless they have agreed to meet?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Does a lion roar in the forest,when he has no prey?Does a young lion
        cry out from his den,if he has taken nothing?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Does a bird fall in a snare on the earth,when there is no trap for
        it?Does a snare spring up from the ground,when it has taken nothing?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  Is a trumpet blown in a city,and the people are not afraid?  Does
        disaster come to a city,unless the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has done it?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CFor the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps> does nothing  without
        revealing his secretto his servants the prophets.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The lion has roared;who will not fear?  The Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>
        has spoken;who can but prophesy?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Proclaim to the strongholds in Ashdodand to the strongholds in the
        land of Egypt,and say, \u201CAssemble yourselves on the mountains of Samaria,and
        see the great tumults within her,and the oppressed in her midst.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CThey do not know how to do right,\u201D declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, 
        \u201Cthose who store up violence and robbery in their strongholds.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>:  \u201CAn
        adversary shall surround the landand bring down[[COMMENT(0)]] your defenses
        from you,and your strongholds shall be plundered.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:11 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: \u201CAs the shepherd
        rescues from the mouth of the lion two legs, or a piece of an ear, so shall
        the people of Israel who dwell in Samaria be rescued, with the corner of
        a couch and part[[COMMENT(0)]] of a bed.  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:12 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew word is uncertain
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CHear, and testify against the house of Jacob,\u201Ddeclares
        the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>, the God of hosts,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201Cthat on the day I punish Israel for his transgressions,  I
        will punish the altars of Bethel,and the horns of the altar shall be cut
        offand fall to the ground.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "  I will strike the winter house along with the summer house,and
        the houses of ivory shall perish,and the great houses[[COMMENT(0)]] shall
        come to an end,\u201Ddeclares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>."
      comments:
      - number: '3:15 '
        content: 'Or '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CHear this word, you cows of Bashan,who are on the mountain
        of Samaria,  who oppress the poor, who crush the needy,who say to your husbands,
        \u2018Bring, that we may drink!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '  The Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps> has sworn by his holinessthat,
        behold, the days are coming upon you,  when they shall take you away with
        hooks,  even the last of you with fishhooks.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "  And you shall go out through the breaches,each one straight ahead;and
        you shall be cast out into Harmon,\u201Ddeclares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "  \u201CCome to Bethel, and transgress;to Gilgal, and multiply transgression; 
        bring your sacrifices every morning,your tithes every three days;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Israel Has Not Returned to the '
      title: 'Israel Has Not Returned to the '
      number: 5
      content: "offer a sacrifice of thanksgiving of that which is leavened,and proclaim
        freewill offerings, publish them;  for so you love to do, O people of Israel!\u201Ddeclares
        the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>.<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CI gave you cleanness of teeth in all your cities,and lack of
        bread in all your places,  yet you did not return to me,\u201Ddeclares the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CI also withheld the rain from youwhen there were yet three
        months to the harvest;  I would send rain on one city,and send no rain on
        another city;one field would have rain,and the field on which it did not
        rain would wither;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "so two or three cities would wander to another cityto drink water,
        and would not be satisfied;  yet you did not return to me,\u201Ddeclares
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "  \u201CI struck you with blight and mildew;your many gardens and
        your vineyards,your fig trees and your olive trees the locust devoured; 
        yet you did not return to me,\u201Ddeclares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CI sent among you a pestilence after the manner of Egypt;I killed
        your young men with the sword,and carried away your horses,[[COMMENT(0)]]and
        I made the stench of your camp go up into your nostrils;  yet you did not
        return to me,\u201Ddeclares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:10 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CI overthrew some of you,  as when God overthrew Sodom and Gomorrah,and
        you were as a brand[[COMMENT(0)]] plucked out of the burning;  yet you did
        not return to me,\u201Ddeclares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:11 '
        content: That is, a burning stick
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CTherefore thus I will do to you, O Israel;because I will do
        this to you,prepare to meet your God, O Israel!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "For behold, he who forms the mountains and creates the wind,and declares
        to man what is his thought,  who makes the morning darkness,and treads on
        the heights of the earth\u2014  the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God
        of hosts, is his name!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Seek the  and Live'
      title: Seek the  and Live
      number: 1
      content: '<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  Hear this word that I take up over you
        in lamentation, O house of Israel:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CFallen, no more to rise,is the virgin Israel;forsaken on her
        land,with none to raise her up.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "For thus says the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>:\u201CThe city
        that went out a thousandshall have a hundred left,and that which went out
        a hundredshall have ten leftto the house of Israel.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> to the house of Israel: 
        \u201CSeek me and live;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "but do not seek Bethel,and do not enter into Gilgalor cross over
        to Beersheba;for Gilgal shall surely go into exile,and Bethel shall come
        to nothing.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  Seek the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and live,  lest he break out
        like fire in the house of Joseph,and it devour, with none to quench it for
        Bethel,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'O you who turn justice to wormwood[[COMMENT(0)]]and cast down righteousness
        to the earth!  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:7 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He who made the Pleiades and Orion,and turns deep darkness into the
        morningand darkens the day into night,who calls for the waters of the sea 
        and pours them out on the surface of the earth,  the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is his name;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  who makes destruction flash forth against the strong,so that destruction
        comes upon the fortress.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  They hate him who reproves in the gate,and they abhor him who speaks
        the truth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Therefore because you trample on[[COMMENT(0)]] the poorand you exact
        taxes of grain from him,  you have built houses of hewn stone,but you shall
        not dwell in them;  you have planted pleasant vineyards,but you shall not
        drink their wine.  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:11 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "For I know how many are your transgressionsand how great are your
        sins\u2014you who afflict the righteous, who take a bribe,and turn aside
        the needy in the gate.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Therefore he who is prudent will keep silent in such a time,  for
        it is an evil time.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  Seek good, and not evil,that you may live;and so the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of hosts, will be with you,as you have said.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  Hate evil, and love good,and establish justice in the gate;  it
        may be that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of hosts,will be gracious
        to the remnant of Joseph.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Therefore thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of hosts,
        the Lord:\u201CIn all the squares there shall be wailing,and in all the streets
        they shall say, \u2018Alas! Alas!\u2019They shall call the farmers to mourningand
        to wailing those who are skilled in lamentation,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Let Justice Roll Down'
      title: Let Justice Roll Down
      number: 17
      content: "and in all vineyards there shall be wailing,for I will pass through
        your midst,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Woe to you who desire the day of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!Why
        would you have the day of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?  It is darkness,
        and not light,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  as if a man fled from a lion,and a bear met him,or went into the
        house and leaned his hand against the wall,and a serpent bit him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '  Is not the day of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> darkness, and
        not light,and gloom with no brightness in it?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "  \u201CI hate, I despise your feasts,and I take no delight in your
        solemn assemblies.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '  Even though you offer me your burnt offerings and grain offerings,I
        will not accept them;and the peace offerings of your fattened animals,I will
        not look upon them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Take away from me the noise of your songs;to the melody of your harps
        I will not listen.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'But let justice roll down like waters,and righteousness like an ever-flowing
        stream.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "  \u201CDid you bring to me sacrifices and offerings during the forty
        years in the wilderness, O house of Israel? "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "You shall take up Sikkuth your king, and Kiyyun your star-god\u2014your
        images that you made for yourselves, "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "and I will send you into exile beyond Damascus,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        whose name is the God of hosts."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Woe to Those at Ease in Zion'
      title: Woe to Those at Ease in Zion
      number: 1
      content: "    \u201CWoe to those who are at ease in Zion,and to those who feel
        secure on the mountain of Samaria,  the notable men of the first of the nations,to
        whom the house of Israel comes!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Pass over to Calneh, and see,and from there go to Hamath the great;then
        go down to Gath of the Philistines.  Are you better than these kingdoms?Or
        is their territory greater than your territory,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  O you who put far away the day of disaster  and bring near the
        seat of violence?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CWoe to those who lie on beds of ivory  and stretch themselves
        out on their couches,and eat lambs from the flock  and calves from the midst
        of the stall,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  who sing idle songs to the sound of the harpand like David invent
        for themselves instruments of music,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  who drink wine in bowlsand anoint themselves with the finest oils,but
        are not grieved over the ruin of Joseph!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "  Therefore they shall now be the first of those who go into exile,and
        the revelry of those who stretch themselves out shall pass away.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "  The Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps> has sworn by himself, declares
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of hosts:\u201CI abhor the pride
        of Jacoband hate his strongholds,  and I will deliver up the city and all
        that is in it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And if ten men remain in one house, they shall die. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And when one\u2019s relative, the one who anoints him for burial,
        shall take him up to bring the bones out of the house, and shall say to him
        who is in the innermost parts of the house, \u201CIs there still anyone with
        you?\u201D he shall say, \u201CNo\u201D; and he shall say, \u201CSilence!
        We must not mention the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For behold, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> commands,and the great
        house shall be struck down into fragments,and the little house into bits.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Do horses run on rocks?Does one plow there[[COMMENT(0)]] with oxen? 
        But you have turned justice into poison  and the fruit of righteousness into
        wormwood\u2014  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:12 '
        content: 'Or Or '
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "you who rejoice in Lo-debar,[[COMMENT(0)]]who say, \u201CHave we
        not by our own strengthcaptured Karnaim for ourselves?\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:13 '
        content: means means (a symbol of strength)
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CFor behold, I will raise up against you a nation,O house of
        Israel,\u201D declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of hosts;\u201Cand
        they shall oppress you from Lebo-hamathto the Brook of the Arabah.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Warning Visions'
      title: Warning Visions
      number: 1
      content: "    This is what the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps> showed me: behold,
        he was forming locusts when the latter growth was just beginning to sprout,
        and behold, it was the latter growth after the king\u2019s mowings. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "When they had finished eating the grass of the land, I said,\u201CO
        Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>, please forgive!  How can Jacob stand?He
        is so small!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> relented concerning this:\u201CIt
        shall not be,\u201D said the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  This is what the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps> showed me: behold,
        the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps> was calling for a judgment by fire, and
        it devoured the great deep and was eating up the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then I said,\u201CO Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>, please cease! 
        How can Jacob stand?He is so small!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> relented concerning this:\u201CThis
        also shall not be,\u201D said the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  This is what he showed me: behold, the Lord was standing beside
        a wall built with a plumb line, with a plumb line in his hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u201CAmos, what
        do you see?\u201D And I said, \u201CA plumb line.\u201D Then the Lord said,\u201CBehold,
        I am setting a plumb linein the midst of my people Israel;  I will never
        again pass by them;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Amos Accused'
      title: Amos Accused
      number: 9
      content: "  the high places of Isaac shall be made desolate,and the sanctuaries
        of Israel shall be laid waste,and I will rise against the house of Jeroboam
        with the sword.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Amaziah the priest of Bethel sent to Jeroboam king of Israel,
        saying, \u201CAmos has conspired against you in the midst of the house of
        Israel. The land is not able to bear all his words. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "For thus Amos has said,\u201C\u2018Jeroboam shall die by the sword,and
        Israel must go into exileaway from his land.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And Amaziah said to Amos, \u201CO seer, go, flee away to the land
        of Judah, and eat bread there, and prophesy there, "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "but never again prophesy at Bethel, for it is the king\u2019s sanctuary,
        and it is a temple of the kingdom.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Amos answered and said to Amaziah, \u201CI was[[COMMENT(0)]]
        no prophet, nor a prophet\u2019s son, but I was a herdsman and a dresser
        of sycamore figs. "
      comments:
      - number: '7:14 '
        content: Or ; twice in this verse
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> took me from following the flock,
        and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u2018Go, prophesy to my
        people Israel.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Now therefore hear the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CYou
        say, \u2018Do not prophesy against Israel,and do not preach against the house
        of Isaac.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "  Therefore thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:\u201C\u2018Your
        wife shall be a prostitute in the city,and your sons and your daughters shall
        fall by the sword,and your land shall be divided up with a measuring line;you
        yourself shall die in an unclean land,and Israel shall surely go into exile
        away from its land.\u2019\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Coming Day of Bitter Mourning'
      title: The Coming Day of Bitter Mourning
      number: 1
      content: '    This is what the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps> showed me: behold,
        a basket of summer fruit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And he said, \u201CAmos, what do you see?\u201D And I said, \u201CA
        basket of summer fruit.\u201D Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to
        me,  \u201CThe end[[COMMENT(0)]] has come upon my people Israel;I will never
        again pass by them.  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:2 '
        content: The Hebrew words for and sound alike
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "  The songs of the temple[[COMMENT(0)]]  shall become wailings in
        that day,\u201Ddeclares the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>.  \u201CSo many
        dead bodies!\u201D\u201CThey are thrown everywhere!\u201D  \u201CSilence!\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:3 '
        content: 'Or Or '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Hear this, you who trample on the needyand bring the poor of the
        land to an end,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "saying, \u201CWhen will the new moon be over,that we may sell grain?And
        the Sabbath,that we may offer wheat for sale,that we may make the ephah small
        and the shekel[[COMMENT(0)]] greatand deal deceitfully with false balances,  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:5 '
        content: An was about 3/5 bushel or 22 liters; a was about 2/5 ounce or 11
          grams
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "that we may buy the poor for silverand the needy for a pair of sandalsand
        sell the chaff of the wheat?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has sworn by the pride of Jacob:\u201CSurely
        I will never forget any of their deeds.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "  Shall not the land tremble on this account,and everyone mourn who
        dwells in it,  and all of it rise like the Nile,and be tossed about and sink
        again, like the Nile of Egypt?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CAnd on that day,\u201D declares the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>, 
        \u201CI will make the sun go down at noonand darken the earth in broad daylight.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  I will turn your feasts into mourningand all your songs into lamentation; 
        I will bring sackcloth on every waist  and baldness on every head;  I will
        make it like the mourning for an only sonand the end of it like a bitter
        day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CBehold, the days are coming,\u201D declares the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>,\u201Cwhen
        I will send a famine on the land\u2014not a famine of bread, nor a thirst
        for water,  but of hearing the words of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '  They shall wander from sea to sea,and from north to east;they shall
        run to and fro, to seek the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,  but
        they shall not find it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "  \u201CIn that day the lovely virgins and the young menshall faint
        for thirst.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Those who swear by the Guilt of Samaria,and say, \u2018As your god
        lives, O Dan,\u2019and, \u2018As the Way of Beersheba lives,\u2019they shall
        fall, and never rise again.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Destruction of Israel'
      title: The Destruction of Israel
      number: 1
      content: "  I saw the Lord standing beside[[COMMENT(0)]] the altar, and he
        said:  \u201CStrike the capitals until the thresholds shake,  and shatter
        them on the heads of all the people;and those who are left of them I will
        kill with the sword;  not one of them shall flee away;not one of them shall
        escape.  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:1 '
        content: 'Or Hebrew '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "  \u201CIf they dig into Sheol,from there shall my hand take them; 
        if they climb up to heaven,from there I will bring them down.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'If they hide themselves on the top of Carmel,from there I will search
        them out and take them;  and if they hide from my sight at the bottom of
        the sea,there I will command the serpent, and it shall bite them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "  And if they go into captivity before their enemies,there I will
        command the sword, and it shall kill them;  and I will fix my eyes upon themfor
        evil and not for good.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps> of hosts,he who touches the earth
        and it melts,and all who dwell in it mourn,  and all of it rises like the
        Nile,  and sinks again, like the Nile of Egypt;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "  who builds his upper chambers in the heavensand founds his vault
        upon the earth;  who calls for the waters of the seaand pours them out upon
        the surface of the earth\u2014  the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is his name.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CAre you not like the Cushites to me,O people of Israel?\u201D
        declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  \u201CDid I not bring up Israel
        from the land of Egypt,and the Philistines from Caphtor and the Syrians from
        Kir?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Behold, the eyes of the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps> are upon
        the sinful kingdom,and I will destroy it from the surface of the ground, 
        except that I will not utterly destroy the house of Jacob,\u201Ddeclares
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CFor behold, I will command,  and shake the house of Israel
        among all the nationsas one shakes with a sieve,but no pebble shall fall
        to the earth.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: The Restoration of Israel'
      title: The Restoration of Israel
      number: 10
      content: "All the sinners of my people shall die by the sword,who say, \u2018Disaster
        shall not overtake or meet us.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CIn that day I will raise upthe booth of David that is fallenand
        repair its breaches,and raise up its ruinsand rebuild it as in the days of
        old,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "  that they may possess the remnant of Edomand all the nations who
        are called by my name,\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        who does this.  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:12 '
        content: 'Hebrew; Septuagint (compare Acts 15:17) '
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CBehold, the days are coming,\u201D declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, 
        \u201Cwhen the plowman shall overtake the reaperand the treader of grapes
        him who sows the seed;  the mountains shall drip sweet wine,and all the hills
        shall flow with it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  I will restore the fortunes of my people Israel,and they shall
        rebuild the ruined cities and inhabit them;  they shall plant vineyards and
        drink their wine,and they shall make gardens and eat their fruit.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "  I will plant them on their land,  and they shall never again be
        uprootedout of the land that I have given them,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God."
      comments: []
